  "prompt": "How can I play DLC on PS4 disc based games?",
  "response": "To play **DLC (Downloadable Content)** on **PS4 disc-based games**, you need to follow these steps:\n\n### 1. **Ensure the Game is Updated**\n   - Insert the game disc into your PS4.\n   - If there\u2019s an update available for the game, the PS4 will prompt you to download it. Make sure the game is fully updated to support the DLC.\n\n### 2. **Purchase or Download the DLC**\n   - Go to the **PlayStation Store** on your PS4 or via the **PlayStation App**.\n   - Search for the game, then look for its DLC in the game\u2019s store page.\n   - Purchase the DLC (if it\u2019s not free) and download it to your PS4.\n\n### 3. **Ensure Compatibility**\n   - The DLC must be from the same region as your game disc. For example, if your game disc is from **Region 1 (North America)**, the DLC must also be from the same region. Region mismatches will prevent the DLC from working.\n\n### 4. **Install the DLC**\n   - Once the DLC is downloaded, it will automatically install on your PS4.\n   - You can check the installation progress in the **Notifications** menu or the **Library** under the game\u2019s page.\n\n### 5. **Access the DLC in the Game**\n   - Launch the game.\n   - The DLC content should now be accessible within the game. This could include new levels, characters, items, or other features depending on the DLC.\n\n### 6. **Keep the Disc Inserted**\n   - Since the game is disc-based, you must always have the disc inserted in the PS4 to play both the base game and the DLC.\n\n### Troubleshooting Tips:\n   - If the DLC doesn\u2019t appear in the game, restart your PS4 and check for updates again.\n   - Ensure your PS4 is connected to the internet during the DLC download and installation process.\n   - If you\u2019re still having issues, contact **PlayStation Support** for assistance.\n\nBy following these steps, you should be able to enjoy your DLC on your PS4 disc-based game!",
